{
  "texts": [
    "The Conv1d network employs the backpropagation optimization process to train its parameters.",
    "This process involves adjusting the network's weights and biases to minimize a loss function, quantifying the discrepancy between the anticipated and observed output.",
    "The CNN model under examination comprises three convolutional layers, three max-pooling layers, two dropout levels, and two fully connected layers.",
    "Dropout is a regularization technique used in deep learning to address the problem of overfitting.",
    "Overfitting occurs when a model becomes excessively complex during training on a limited dataset, fitting the noise rather than the underlying pattern."
  ]
}